-- Enstar Discloses Material Internal Control Weakness Tied to Deal
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2013-08-09T20:30:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-09/enstar-discloses-material-internal-control-weakness-tied-to-deal.html
Enstar Group Ltd., the firm that
assumes risks from insurers seeking to exit businesses, said it
identified a material weakness in its internal controls related
to bonds tied to a deal completed this year.  “The company has taken steps to remediate its internal
control over financial reporting,” Hamilton, Bermuda-based
Enstar said today in a regulatory filing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
